Create EC2 instance - Docker host
-> Subnet - 1a
-> SG - Docker-Sg
-> 12Gib
--> Launch Instance

# hostnamectl set-hostname docker.example.com
# bash
# yum install docker
# docker info
# systemctl start docker
# systemctl enable docker
# docker pull ubuntu
# docker run -it --name web-app -p 8080:80 ubuntu:latest /bin/bash
> inside Container
# apt update -y
# apt install apache2 -y
# cd /var/www/html
# echo "this is my web-app running on docker" > index.html
# service apache2 start


// Nginx
# docker pull nginx
# docker run -it --name nginx-app -p 8080:80 nginx:latest /bin/bash
> inside container
# service nginx start
# cd /usr/share/nginx/html
# echo "I'm Dev" >index.html
# service nginx start

> Copy public IP > paste along with port
!! Allow port in SG

